Sudoku Solver

A C++ application that solves a 9×9 Sudoku puzzle using the Backtracking Algorithm. The program accepts a Sudoku grid as input, fills empty cells, and displays the completed solution while following Sudoku rules.

Features

Solves standard 9×9 Sudoku puzzles

Uses Backtracking Algorithm

Accepts user input for custom puzzles

Displays solved Sudoku grid

Efficient and easy to use


Technologies Used

C++

Recursion

Backtracking Algorithm


How to Run

1. Compile the source code using a C++ compiler.


2. Run the executable.


3. Enter the Sudoku puzzle (use 0 for empty cells).


4. The program will display the solved Sudoku grid.



Project Objective

This project demonstrates the use of recursion and backtracking techniques to solve constraint-based problems efficiently.
